<html>
<body>
Reports exceptions that are thrown by top-level JSP scriptlets.<br/>

<p><b>Example:</b></p>
<pre><code lang="jsp">
  &lt;%!
  String getFormattedDate() {
    ...
    throw new IllegalArgumentException(...); // Error
  }
  %&gt;
  &lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Hello, JSP!&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
  &lt;i&gt;Today is &lt;%= getFormattedDate() %&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
  &lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre><br/>

<!-- tooltip end -->
<p>
  <b>NOTE:</b> Such JSP pages will compile, because the servlet container wraps
  all JSP code in a <b>try {} catch() {}</b> block,
  but they will produce runtime exceptions when deployed on the server.
</p>
</body>
</html>
